Now why is it so difficult for a warrior to understand bashing is a good thing. Sometimes the damage you pervent is more important then the damage you do. i was on these raid where the caster mobs could not be stunned by magic. The only way to stun was bash them mobs. After 5 attemp at the mobs to chain stun. the clerics and the chanter /ooc that the mob cannot be stun by magic. The Maintank on the next pulled after the /ooc was made with &quot;start casting stun at it&quot;. The mains cleric said no it's a waste of mana we can not stun it. I /ooc get out your shielda and start bashing. ummm I saw no weapons change to shield. Next pull the big old nasty head chanter mob was pulled. I cast a stun. Resist. I cast a nuke resist. Now after A TPW I told my warriors in my group who were not the main group they should be bashing. One of the 2 warriors in the group response was &quot;it's not my job to bash&quot;. I disbanded the group and wait for a rez. Now in the raid we had no pallies or SKs. So who job is it to bash when you have 6 warriors and the big ol caster mob needs to be stunned? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ulvydro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lvydro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/17/02 6:20:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=825.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;it's not my job to bash&quot;</span><hr size=1> it is NOT a warriors job to bash... if one of the warriors is 55+ their kick would stun but im sorry unless they were ogre/troll/barbarian warriors you have no right to ask them to bash... ghetto bashing is a pain in the ass <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.e