Proud member of Prism<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ufaervas1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faervas1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/17/02 8:39:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=825.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> &quot;it's not my job to bash&quot;</span><hr size=1> If you are not the Main tank, your job is to do what it takes to win the fight. When a mob is AOEing and hitting the clerics and chanters druids wizards, it puts a stress on the healer. Who now has to make sure more then the main needs healing. If  I'm too busy healing the chanter druid wizard myself it takes time and mana I need to make sure the maintank and my tanks are healed. Your job is to make sure I can do mine. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utunnelratx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TunnelRatX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/17/02 9:27:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=825.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fearlessblack.net/images/Maulo002.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;it's not my job to bash&quot;</span><hr size=1> I personally hate casting mobs. I slam or bash a mob when needed. Caster mobs tend to a pain in the ass. Gating, then getting X number of friends upon return, mass AOE, etc. It like what Faervas1 said &quot;do what it takes to win the fight&quot;. If the job calls for you too bash the mob. Bash the mob. Not everyone is wearing 100% MR gear. Just my two cents.<br>
