 -G.A. Custer</center></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usanchek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sanchek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/17/02 9:52:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=825.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;it's not my job to bash&quot;</span><hr size=1> There isn't a whole lotta point in getting conditioned to think that a melee is going to stop a mob from casting, at higher level, if a caster can't.  55+ mobs aren't stunnable, bashable, slamable, or whatever-elseable.  If it's important, depend on sieve.  Sieve is unresistable.  Against many mobs, a level 34 enchanter is much more effective than the most uber level 60 warrior, when it comes to preventing spell casting. <p><br>
